  "semantics": [
    "Consumer-provided symbols remain inventoried with exact declaration provenance but are external rather than pending private-JSC work.",
    "zig-js must not define a duplicate symbol that collides when the pinned consumer supplies its host-runtime provider objects.",
    "EventLoopTaskNoContext creator lookup is non-consuming; task performance invokes the callback and then self-deletes the task.",
    "Termination providers close consumer-owned WebView and SQLite state before their backing runtime is dismantled.",
    "Debugger providers retain the consumer's script-context identity and thread-start ordering.",
    "Loader, plugin, scheduler, and worker providers keep consumer-owned host state and callback types outside the JavaScriptCore shim.",
    "Home and Bun may pin different provider-file bytes while sharing the same imported Zig declarations.",
    "After this classification Bun has no pending private imports; Home retains only JSC__SourceProvider__deref."
  ]
